The paper deals with time series classification using a convolutional network and adversarial regularization to learn interpretable shapelets. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional networks suggests a possible association with computer vision (cs.CV) and the use of adversarial regularization suggests a possible association with neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
